The fried food here is good but their customer service is terrible. Business owners are always the first ones to cry about supporting small businesses but don’t know the first thing on running one. We have ordered here numerous times in person, door dash and seamless but today my husband went in person, paid cash and tipped and they forgot our drink. When we called to ask if they can send someone over since it was their fault, the lady’s response on the phone was “wooow”. My husband went to pick it up since he paid cash and would not be able to get a refund over the phone but this is the last time we order from this place. Just because you’re in the ghetto, doesn’t mean you have to be ghetto. Treat your customers well if you want small business support.
